    "created_at": "2014-03-23T08:38:41Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-03-23T08:38:55Z",
    "body": "I don't take issue with the overall proposal, just this part. It's an unreliable way of catching unbounded growth because it relies on a hard-wired magic number. It's not possible to account for the amount of available memory and the program's design.\n\nIf it's a debugging feature, then I don't think it should throw a failure. A failure can be caught, so it's a runtime feature that will be relied upon - even if it's not reliably thrown.\n",
